Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Peel and thinly slice @garlic{1%clove}. Strip @thyme{1/4%oz} leaves from stems until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings).

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and season with @salt and @pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

Once water is boiling, gently add @mushroom ravioli{9%oz} to #pot. Immediately reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve 1/3 cup pasta cooking water (½ cup for 4 servings), then drain. Keep empty pot handy for step 4.

Heat a large drizzle of cooking oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add shallot, garlic, and @grape tomatoes{8%oz}. Lightly season with salt and pepper. Cook, gently pressing on tomatoes as they begin to soften, until shallot starts to caramelize and tomatoes are lightly blistered, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Use pan used for chicken or turkey here.

Add reserved pasta cooking water to #pot used for pasta over medium-high heat; bring to a simmer. Whisk in @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, and @cream cheese{2%tbsp} until smooth. Continue to cook, whisking, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add thyme leaves and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings); cook until thyme is fragrant and butter has melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Add drained ravioli to pan with sauce; gently toss until thoroughly coated. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and top with tomato mixture. Serve.

Stir in chicken along with ravioli.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.